8DjYjnplEmXCHy3dJYwqPkkeS-AVBGLip68ZJMojdQMxdtMcAbLrevsu6AnIjQ==\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering native-image entry**\\n\\nI’m exploring the idea that the generated main entry for native-image could be linked to `*Test` classes known at compile time. I wonder if creating a new file would help. Maybe I need to check if ClassUtilTest was discovered because it wasn’t included in `nativeTest`, but that doesn't seem to be the issue. I'm also thinking coverage could be affected if a source filter is excluding the test path. It's tricky!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Figuring out access methods**\\n\\nI'm considering using `MethodHandles.lookup()` as an alternative since it allows dynamic access without direct reflection. However, I'm questioning whether this approach applies to the test rather than the library itself. It seems that using it would also exercise the ClassUtil method, which is interesting. I wonder about the notion of a public API needing it; it feels like that's not accurate here, given the class has a public static method but is package-private.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering exception handling**\\n\\nI'm thinking about how to handle the newInstance constructor. If metadata is missing, it might throw a normal BadPaddingException. But on the JVM, I should be careful because it could also lead to an AEADBadTagException. It's important to differentiate these two situations to manage exceptions effectively. I need to make sure I understand the implications of both exceptions and handle them appropriately.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_jjUHpj32gvcjJwOeGjY3P96b|fc_0d95974c093935170169f9ed634de88195987b2faa6b13a889", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bc-fips/2.1.2/src/test/java/org_bouncycastle/bc_fips/ClassUtilTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertNotNull;\nimport static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertThrows;\n", "newText": "import static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertInstanceOf;\nimport static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertNotNull;\nimport static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertThrows;\n"}, {"oldText": "import java.security.Provider;\nimport java.util.Arrays;\n", "newText": "import java.security.Provider;\nimport java.security.Security;\nimport java.util.Arrays;\n"}, {"oldText": "        Provider provider = new BouncyCastleFipsProvider();\n        Provider.Service gcmService = provider.getService(\"Cipher\", \"GCM\");\n        assertNotNull(gcmService);\n        assertNotNull(gcmService.newInstance(null));\n\n        SecretKeySpec key = new SecretKeySpec(KEY_BYTES, \"AES\");\n        GCMParameterSpec parameterSpec = new GCMParameterSpec(128, IV);\n        byte[] plaintext = \"authenticated plaintext\".getBytes(StandardCharsets.UTF_8);\n\n        Cipher encryptCipher = Cipher.getInstance(\"AES/GCM/NoPadding\", provider);\n        encryptCipher.init(Cipher.ENCRYPT_MODE, key, parameterSpec);\n        byte[] ciphertext = encryptCipher.doFinal(plaintext);\n\n        Cipher decryptCipher = Cipher.getInstance(\"AES/GCM/NoPadding\", provider);\n        decryptCipher.init(Cipher.DECRYPT_MODE, key, parameterSpec);\n        byte[] decrypted = decryptCipher.doFinal(ciphertext);\n        assertArrayEquals(plaintext, decrypted);\n\n        byte[] tamperedCiphertext = Arrays.copyOf(ciphertext, ciphertext.length);\n        tamperedCiphertext[tamperedCiphertext.length - 1] ^= 0x01;\n\n        Cipher tamperedDecryptCipher = Cipher.getInstance(\"AES/GCM/NoPadding\", provider);\n        tamperedDecryptCipher.init(Cipher.DECRYPT_MODE, key, parameterSpec);\n        AEADBadTagException exception = assertThrows(\n                AEADBadTagException.class,\n                () -> tamperedDecryptCipher.doFinal(tamperedCiphertext));\n        assertNotNull(exception.getMessage());\n", "newText": "        Provider provider = new BouncyCastleFipsProvider();\n        Security.addProvider(provider);\n        try {\n            Provider.Service gcmService = provider.getService(\"Cipher\", \"GCM\");\n            assertNotNull(gcmService);\n\n            SecretKeySpec key = new SecretKeySpec(KEY_BYTES, \"AES\");\n            GCMParameterSpec parameterSpec = new GCMParameterSpec(128, IV);\n            byte[] plaintext = \"authenticated plaintext\".getBytes(StandardCharsets.UTF_8);\n\n            Cipher encryptCipher = Cipher.getInstance(\"GCM\", BouncyCastleFipsProvider.PROVIDER_NAME);\n            encryptCipher.init(Cipher.ENCRYPT_MODE, key, parameterSpec);\n            byte[] ciphertext = encryptCipher.doFinal(plaintext);\n\n            Cipher decryptCipher = Cipher.getInstance(\"GCM\", BouncyCastleFipsProvider.PROVIDER_NAME);\n            decryptCipher.init(Cipher.DECRYPT_MODE, key, parameterSpec);\n            byte[] decrypted = decryptCipher.doFinal(ciphertext);\n            assertArrayEquals(plaintext, decrypted);\n\n            byte[] tamperedCiphertext = Arrays.copyOf(ciphertext, ciphertext.length);\n            tamperedCiphertext[tamperedCiphertext.length - 1] ^= 0x01;\n\n            Cipher tamperedDecryptCipher = Cipher.getInstance(\"GCM\", BouncyCastleFipsProvider.PROVIDER_NAME);\n            tamperedDecryptCipher.init(Cipher.DECRYPT_MODE, key, parameterSpec);\n            AEADBadTagException exception = assertThrows(\n                    AEADBadTagException.class,\n                    () -> tamperedDecryptCipher.doFinal(tamperedCiphertext));\n            assertInstanceOf(AEADBadTagException.class, exception);\n            assertNotNull(exception.getMessage());\n        } finally {\n            Security.removeProvider(BouncyCastleFipsProvider.PROVIDER_NAME);\n        }\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1282, "output": 2569, "cacheRead": 44032, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 47883, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777986890415, "responseId": "resp_0d95974c093935170169f9ed4b02148195ac4833eb97c20b0b"}}
