Provider can be registered if there's already one with the same name from another test running in parallel. If both Bc_fipsTest and ClassUtilTest are operating, it might not create issues. But since the security provider is global, removing it in the finally block could affect others. Regarding coding style, Checkstyle might prevent having `try {` on the same line, following Java conventions. I'll steer clear of modifying untracked metadata and inspect it instead.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Investigating Cipher issues**\\n\\nI’m pondering whether I need to use a direct call through the public API, specifically `Provider.Service.newInstance`, which returns the BaseCipher.Builder for class initialization and lookup. I’ve removed the newInstance method, but maybe I should consider re-adding it. While it won’t address throwBadTag, it could assist with GcmSpecUtil. However, it may fail due to FipsStatus. I wonder if it's also because `Cipher.getInstance` is utilizing a service that hasn’t been created yet?\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Refined the active-class test again to make the `ClassUtil` path more direct through Bouncy Castle FIPS’ own registered JCA service.\n\nUpdated:\n- `tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bc-fips/2.1.2/src/test/java/org_bouncycastle/bc_fips/ClassUtilTest.java`\n\nKey changes:\n- Registers `BouncyCastleFipsProvider` with `Security`.\n- Resolves the provider’s explicit `Cipher.GCM` service.\n- Uses `Cipher.getInstance(\"GCM\", BouncyCastleFipsProvider.PROVIDER_NAME)` instead of the transformation alias.\n- Performs a successful AES/GCM round trip.\n- Tampers with the authentication tag and asserts `AEADBadTagException`, targeting the `ClassUtil.throwBadTagException(...)` path.\n\nAlso retained the earlier visibility fixes for the existing placeholder test class.\n\nI did not run tests or modify metadata/native-image configuration.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0d95974c093935170169f9eda4ffc88195956f30e6a4f4ae12\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 509, "output": 1400, "cacheRead": 50176, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 52085, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1777986959942, "responseId": "resp_0d95974c093935170169f9ed909d208195a974d7c7f9cb0a80"}}
[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Thinking through exceptions**\n\nI'm considering whether `InstantiationException` is missing in the native context, as it may lead to falling to `BadPaddingException`. It seems if the assertion for `AEADBadTagException` fails, the native process might encounter issues. However, the workflow might be generating metadata outside the Java agent. Tests should ideally run under the Native Image, so I think asserting both `BadPaddingException` and possibly using `assertNotNull` is necessary. There’s a lot to unpack here!\n\n**Considering Java security provider issues**\n\nI'm thinking about whether the BouncyCastleFipsProvider can be registered if there's already one with the same name from another test running in parallel. If both Bc_fipsTest and ClassUtilTest are operating, it might not create issues. But since the security provider is global, removing it in the finally block could affect others. Regarding coding style, Checkstyle might prevent having `try {` on the same line, following Java conventions. I'll steer clear of modifying untracked metadata and inspect it instead.\n\n**Investigating Cipher issues**\n\nI’m pondering whether I need to use a direct call through the public API, specifically `Provider.Service.newInstance`, which returns the BaseCipher.Builder for class initialization and lookup. I’ve removed the newInstance method, but maybe I should consider re-adding it. While it won’t address throwBadTag, it could assist with GcmSpecUtil. However, it may fail due to FipsStatus. I wonder if it's also because `Cipher.getInstance` is utilizing a service that hasn’t been created yet?", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0d95974c093935170169f9ed9288e4819588447dc97344632f\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp-e2lSr7yn29ERHbDukzL3vVEHV281mboapfl7S5qb65r1cZvjhhscBNWECRa220TUb9KUJde-uEUDbpPWy27AJVyUM43aqvri45-00j5oVLcivOg3MUjaKmKeUPsbhEGoCAWf